South Africa heart surgeon Barnard to be dad at 74 . South African heart transplant pioneer Christiaan Barnard is to become a father for the sixth time at the age of 74 , the Afrikaans - language newspaper Die Burger said on Wednesday . It quoted Barnard ' s third wife , 32 - year - old Karin , as saying their second baby is due in March . " We are very excited . . . The baby was planned , " she told the newspaper . Barnard made history on December 3 , 1967 , when he performed the world ' s first human heart transplant in Cape Town , where he and his wife now live . In recent years he has been involved in research on anti - ageing medications . 
